%N A120425 a(n) = maximum value among all k where 1<=k<=n of GCD(k,ceiling(n/k)).
%H A120425 Robert Israel, <a href="/A120425/b120425.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%e A120425 For n = 10, we have the pairs {k,ceiling(n/k)} of {1,10},{2,5},{3,4},{4,3},{5,2},{6,2},{7,2},{8,2},{9,2},{10,1}. The GCD's of these 10 pairs are 1,1,1,1,1,2,1,2,1,1. Of these, 2 is the largest. So a(10) = 2.
%p A120425 f:= proc(n) local k; max(seq(igcd(k,ceil(n/k)),k=1..n)) end proc:
%p A120425 map(f, [$1..100]);  # _Robert Israel_, Mar 01 2026
%t A120425 Table[Max[Table[GCD[k, Ceiling[n/k]], {k, 1, n}]], {n, 1, 100}] (* _Stefan Steinerberger_, Jul 22 2006 *)
%K A120425 nonn,look,changed
